# 📈 AI Stock Price Prediction (LSTM)

A deep learning-based project that predicts stock prices using **Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)** networks. This project leverages historical stock data to model temporal dependencies and forecast future trends.

---

## 🚀 Features

* 📊 Historical stock data collection using Yahoo Finance
* 🧠 LSTM-based deep learning model for time series prediction
* 🔍 Data preprocessing and normalization
* 📉 Visualization of actual vs predicted stock prices
* ⚡ Scalable and modular code structure

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Python
* TensorFlow / Keras
* NumPy & Pandas
* Matplotlib / Seaborn / Plotly
* yFinance API

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
AI-Stock-Price-Prediction/
│── data/                 # Dataset files (if any)
│── models/               # Saved models
│── notebooks/            # Jupyter notebooks
│── src/                  # Source code
│── requirements.txt      # Dependencies
│── README.md             # Project documentation
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/manpreet-git-hub/AI-Stock-Price-Prediction.git
cd AI-Stock-Price-Prediction
```

2. Create a virtual environment (recommended):

```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate     # For Linux/Mac
venv\Scripts\activate        # For Windows
```

3. Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## ▶️ Usage

Run the main script or notebook:

```bash
python main.py
```

or open Jupyter Notebook:

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

---

## 📊 Model Details

* Uses **LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)** neural network
* Captures long-term dependencies in stock price data
* Trained on historical closing prices
* Data scaled using MinMaxScaler for better performance

